<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-47-0008 </DOCNO><TEXT>The purpose of this document is to provide a reference for use by thoseinterested in the development of renewable energy resources regardingthe extent to which Petroleum Violation Escrow (PVE) funds might be employedby states to fund research, development, demonstration and applicationspertaining to such resources. The document highlights the backgroundand status of the PVE funds being disbursed through state energy agenciesand summarizes the types of energy-related activities being conductedwith these funds and the processes used to select and approve these activities.These funds may provide a mechanism for expanding the contribution ofrenewable energy technologies to domestic energy conservation and security.2 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>